{"id": "nqh1665702549702", "title": "I/O Message Levels", "breadcrumbs": ["Uniface Reference", "Messages Reference", "I/O Message Levels"], "url": "https://docs.rocketsoftware.com/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nqh1665702549702.html", "html": "<html><body><header class=\"zDocsTopicPageHead\"><h1 class=\"css-g931ng\">I/O Message Levels</h1><div class=\"zDocsTopicActions\" role=\"list\"><div class=\"zDocsBundlePagination\" data-testid=\"next-prev-container\" role=\"listitem\"><div class=\"zDocsPrevTopicButton zDocsPrevTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Previous:  Messages Reference \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Previous:  Messages Reference \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ott1665703274332.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-prev\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-prev\"></use></svg></a></span></div><div class=\"zDocsNextTopicButton zDocsNextTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Next: Message Level 1: Store Sequence Messages \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Next: Message Level 1: Store Sequence Messages \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zll1665702716203.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></a></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsMyDocsMenu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Add to My Topics\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Add to My Topics\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" id=\"addToMyDocsDropdownTrigger\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg>Add to My Topics</span><div aria-labelledby=\"pdfDropdown\" class=\"dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right\"><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/nqh1665702549702.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub\">Add selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/nqh1665702549702.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub_head\">Add Topic &amp; Subtopics with topic head</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/nqh1665702549702.html?finish_action=mydocs_pub\">Add entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsWatchButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Watch\" class=\"d-lg-flex d-none zDocsSubscribeButton\" data-tooltip-content=\"Watch\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsSubscribeButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye zDocsSubscribeButton\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsSubscribeButton\">Watch</span></span></div><div class=\"zDocsExportPdfMenu zDocsExportMenu\" data-testid=\"export-pdf-menu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Download PDF\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Download PDF\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530384\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530384\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 17, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nqh1665702549702.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nqh1665702549702.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nqh1665702549702.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"nqh1665702549702\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">I/O Message Levels\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"nqh1665702549702__i_o_message_levels_491037\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Most of the messages that display in the message frame are determined by the I/O\n      message level. The I/O message is a number that is determined by adding up the codes of the\n      applicable message types. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nqh1665702549702__p_d151898e1_d151899e1_d151900e1\">The format of each message is determined by the DBMS connector being used, but the information is similar.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nqh1665702549702__topic_d109432e1_d109433e1_d109434e1_d109435e1_d109436e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d257122e56\">Setting Message Levels</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nqh1665702549702__p_d151904e1_d151905e1_d151906e1\">Set the I/O message level in any of the following\n            ways:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nqh1665702549702__li_d52838e1_d52839e1_d52840e1\">Starting the application with the \n               <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"unz1665702549564.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/unz1665702549564.html\" title=\"Specify the types of messages sent to the message frame or log file.\">/pri</a> command line switch.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nqh1665702549702__li_d52841e1_d52842e1_d52843e1\">In the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">I/O Message Level</span>\n               property of a character-mode application shell. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"apf1705474154305.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/apf1705474154305.html\" title=\"Create a shell for Uniface applications that run in character mode on any supported platform, such as Unix or Linux.\">Define a Character Mode Application Shell</a>.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nqh1665702549702__li_d52844e1_d52845e1_d52846e1\">Using the \n               <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kyc1665702707205.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kyc1665702707205.html\" title=\"Return or set the message level in the message frame.\">$ioprint</a>\n               assignment setting.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nqh1665702549702__li_d52847e1_d52848e1_d52849e1\">Using the ProcScript function \n               <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kyc1665702707205.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kyc1665702707205.html\" title=\"Return or set the message level in the message frame.\">$ioprint</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nqh1665702549702__topic_d109437e1_d109438e1_d109439e1_d109440e1_d109441e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d257122e111\">Message Level Codes </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Message Codes for Uniface I/O</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__1\"> Code </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__2\"> Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__1\"> 1 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__2\">Store\n\t\t\t\t sequence messages. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zll1665702716203.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zll1665702716203.html\" title=\"These messages show whether the entity is being updated or inserted (Store) or deleted (Delete), or whether the named referential integrity constraint is being applied to a many entity.\">Message Level 1: Store Sequence Messages</a>.\n                                               </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__1\"> 2 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__2\"> Connector requests. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ehf1665702716336.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ehf1665702716336.html\" title=\"These messages provide different types of information depending on the connector request issued.\">Message Level 2: DBMS Connector Requests</a>.\n                                               </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__1\"> 4 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__2\"> Return values from Fetch and Select connector requests. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yqr1665702717171.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yqr1665702717171.html\" title=\"These messages show either the number of hits selected, or the length of the I/O buffer fetched. If there is enough room, this information is included on the same line as the connector function call messages. Otherwise, it displays on another line.\">Message Level 4: Return Values from Fetch and Select Connector Requests</a>.\n                                               </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__1\"> 8 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__2\"> Description from Open connector request. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"byl1665702717240.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/byl1665702717240.html\" title=\"This message shows the values used by the connector when opening the file or table. This information is used primarily for debugging DBMS connectors.\">Message Level 8: Description Block from Open Connector Request</a>.\n                                               </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__1\"> 16 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__2\"> Descriptions from the\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">where</code>,<code class=\"ph codeph\">order</code>, and <code class=\"ph codeph\">by</code>\n                     clauses. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"oic1665702717312.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/oic1665702717312.html\" title=\"These messages show which where and order by clauses are generated by Uniface.\">Message Level 16: Descriptions From where and order by Clauses</a>. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__1\"> 32 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__2\"> Generated SQL (if available). For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zxv1665702717381.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zxv1665702717381.html\" title=\"These messages show the SQL instructions generated by Uniface to execute I/O. This information is only available with SQL-based DBMSs.\">Message Level 32: Generated SQL</a>.\n                                               </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__1\"> 64 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__2\"> All system calls Uniface sends to operating system. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"rnp1665702717449.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rnp1665702717449.html\" title=\"These messages show all the system calls, or subprocesses that Uniface starts at the operating system level, such as spools, spawns, and so on.\">Message Level 64: All System Calls Uniface Sends to Operating System</a>.\n                                               </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__1\"> 128 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__2\"> All calls to global objects and descriptors. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"axy1665702717519.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/axy1665702717519.html\" title=\"These messages record all calls for signatures (entity and component descriptors) and global objects.\">Message Level 128: All Calls to Global Objects and Descriptors</a>.\n                                               </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__1\"> 1024 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__2\"> Network messages </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__1\"> 2048 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nqh1665702549702__table_d18308e1_d18309e1_d18310e1__entry__2\">Image loader information </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rlu1665702707277.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Runtime Messages and Log Files</a><p>All Uniface applications can be configured to create log files that collect runtime messages generated during the application session. The messages may be generated by ProcScript commands in your application, or by Uniface to document actions, events, warnings and errors. You can configure which Uniface runtime messages are reported.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zii1665702717603.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>ProcScript Tracing Messages</a><p>When the Debugger tracing setting is set to value 16 (trace all activate information), the $procerrorcontext information for the some errors appears in the message frame.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/unz1665702549564.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/pri</a><p>Specify the types of messages sent to the message frame or log file.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kyc1665702707205.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$ioprint</a><p>Return or set the message level in the message frame.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530384\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530384\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "I/O Message Levels Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 17, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 I/O Message Levels Most of the messages that display in the message frame are determined by the I/O message level. The I/O message is a number that is determined by adding up the codes of the applicable message types. The format of each message is determined by the DBMS connector being used, but the information is similar. Setting Message Levels Set the I/O message level in any of the following ways: Starting the application with the /pri command line switch. In the I/O Message Level property of a character-mode application shell. For more information, see Define a Character Mode Application Shell . Using the $ioprint assignment setting. Using the ProcScript function $ioprint . Message Level Codes Table 1. Message Codes for Uniface I/O Code Description 1 Store sequence messages. For more information, see Message Level 1: Store Sequence Messages . 2 Connector requests. For more information, see Message Level 2: DBMS Connector Requests . 4 Return values from Fetch and Select connector requests. For more information, see Message Level 4: Return Values from Fetch and Select Connector Requests . 8 Description from Open connector request. For more information, see Message Level 8: Description Block from Open Connector Request . 16 Descriptions from the where , order , and by clauses. For more information, see Message Level 16: Descriptions From where and order by Clauses . 32 Generated SQL (if available). For more information, see Message Level 32: Generated SQL . 64 All system calls Uniface sends to operating system. For more information, see Message Level 64: All System Calls Uniface Sends to Operating System . 128 All calls to global objects and descriptors. For more information, see Message Level 128: All Calls to Global Objects and Descriptors . 1024 Network messages 2048 Image loader information Related Links Runtime Messages and Log Files All Uniface applications can be configured to create log files that collect runtime messages generated during the application session. The messages may be generated by ProcScript commands in your application, or by Uniface to document actions, events, warnings and errors. You can configure which Uniface runtime messages are reported. ProcScript Tracing Messages When the Debugger tracing setting is set to value 16 (trace all activate information), the $procerrorcontext information for the some errors appears in the message frame. /pri Specify the types of messages sent to the message frame or log file. $ioprint Return or set the message level in the message frame. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}